//JavaScript and Node.js are single-threaded, which means they execute one task at a time on the main thread.


//Event Loop

Event Loop is a mechanism in JavaScript that checks whether the main thread is free and then executes pending asynchronous tasks.

// THREAD POOL:

A Thread Pool is a collection of worker threads that handle heavy or slow operations in the background.

Why is it Needed?

JavaScript is single-threaded, so it can execute only one task at a time.

If a task takes a long time (like reading a large file), JavaScript would become blocked.

To avoid this, Node.js sends such tasks to the Thread Pool.



