// req.on; 
In Node.js, req.on() is used to listen for events on the request object (req).

Syntax
req.on(eventName, callbackFunction);
req → Request object.
on → Method used to attach an event listener.
eventName → Name of the event ('data', 'end', etc.).
callbackFunction → Function that runs when the event occurs.


